<item>
            <title>[AMQ-2441] TimeStampingBrokerPlugin Not Working on Fuse 5.3.0.4</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-2441</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Due to the adding of the new properties to TimeStampingBrokerPlugin the &quot;message.setTimestamp()&quot; was misplaced and is set to early in the code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The line need to be placed as the last line in the method send() as was in 5.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition the Plugin doesn&apos;t handle the scenario where the Broker is running &quot;behind&quot; its client. What is happening is that it&apos;s setting the Expiration and TimeStamp to historical values in the client perspective causing them to be discarded by the clients.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have supplied a patch that solves both issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
